ce:section.ce:para:
After successful preparation of the Fc-containing polymer, GQDs-PolyFc nanohybrid was synthesized through a facile, fast and physical mixing approach (Scheme 2
                        ). The Fc-containing polymer stacked well to GQDs through the hydrogen bonding among oxygen containing functional groups (-OH and -COOH) and π-π interactions between Fc rings and π bonds of GQDs (Fig. 3
                        ). Finally, a simple physical mixing method was utilized for the synthesis of the binary and ternary nanocomposites. The preparation of the nanocomposites can be explained by strong hydrogen bonding, π-π interactions, and electrostatic interactions between each component (Fig. 3).
